canonical:
  title: 賀表
  author: 李元膺
  language: lzh
  text: 曰爲改歲屬萬物之資生咸造在庭賀一人之有慶凡在普率罔不懽忻中賀 恭惟皇帝躬御泰來功參乾始撫五辰而大順與時偕行制六合以儼臨惟動丕應適履三陽之候益膺萬壽之祺臣職在奉藩心存戀闕比北辰之居所莫遂親瞻如南山之不騫唯申善祝
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀表
  author: 李元膺
  language: lzh
  text: 曰爲改歲。屬萬物之資生。咸造在庭。賀一人之有慶。凡在普率。罔不懽忻。中賀。 恭惟皇帝。躬御泰來。功參乾始。撫五辰而大順。與時偕行。制六合以儼臨。惟動丕應。適履三陽之候。益膺萬壽之祺。臣職在奉藩。心存戀闕。比北辰之居所。莫遂親瞻。如南山之不騫。唯申善祝。
korean:
  title: 하례하는 표
  author: 이원응
  language: kor
  text: 해가 바뀌어 만물이 자생(資生)하는 때 만국이 모두 대궐 뜰에 모여 임금님의 경사를 하례하오니, 하늘 밑, 땅 위의 만 백성들이 모두 기뻐 춤추나이다. 중하(中賀) 공손히 생각건대, 황제께서 몸소 태래(泰來)에 임어(臨御)하시고 공(功)이 건원(乾元)에 참여하시어 오신(五辰)을 어루만져 크게 순(順)하시며 때와 더불어 함께 행하고, 육합(六合)을 제압하여 엄연히 군림(君臨)하시니 움직이는 대로 크게 응하며, 마침 삼양(三陽)이 회복하는 때를 당하셨으니 더욱 만수(萬壽)의 복을 받으시리이다. 신의 직책이 번국(藩國)에 있사오나 마음은 항상 대궐을 그리워함이 비유하건대 북신(北辰)이 그 자리에 있음과 같습니다. 친히 뵈옵지 못하오나, 남산(南山)이 이지러지지 않음처럼 수(壽)하시기를 오직 축원할 뿐입니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0340_010_0440&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: A Respectful Commemoration
  author: Lee Won-eung
  language: eng
  text: |-
    As the year transforms and all things flourish anew,
    The myriad nations gather in the imperial court,
    Offering felicitations for the sovereign's auspicious fortune.
    Beneath the heavens, across the earth, all people rejoice,
    Their hearts dancing with boundless delight.

    In reverent contemplation, I behold the Emperor
    Who stands in supreme harmony with the heavens,
    His virtue participating in the very genesis of creation.
    With graceful touch upon the five celestial bodies,
    He brings great order to all things;
    Moving in perfect accord with the seasons.
    He rules the six directions with majestic authority,
    And his every action yields profound response.

    Now, as the three solar periods return,
    May he receive the blessings of endless years.

    Though my station binds me to a distant region,
    My heart eternally turns toward the palace.
    Like the North Star fixed in its celestial sphere,
    I cannot draw near to behold the sacred presence.
    Yet like the Southern Mountain that shall never waver,
    I offer only steadfast wishes for the Emperor's longevity.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The North Star and Southern Mountain are classical Chinese symbols of permanence and stability, often applied to the emperor and cosmic order.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'three solar periods' (三陽) refer to the three winter months when yang energy begins to return, symbolizing renewal and the emperor's renewed vigor.
